<br>
as far as I've seen, the best path to take (no pun intended) to fix pathing would be the indifferent pets.<br>
<br>
as far as wizard damage / mage damage goes, It's my opinion that a mage + pet should be more over time than a wizard. In 30 seconds, however, a wizzard should out damage a mage two fold.<br>
<br>
the best way I could equate it to melee classes would be this:<br>
<br>
mage + pet = rogue<br>
wizzard = warrior<br>
necro w/ time to get all their DoT's off = monk (i put them here cause they both seem to have a lot of good sides, without so many of the downsides)<br>
mage - pet = bard<br>
<br>
well, roughly anyway... in the time it takes to go from FM to OOM, mages and wizzards should both outdamage at least a warrior. I have yet to hear a compelling arguement otherwise. Maybe you can help me change my views?<br>
<br>
And trust me, mages are NOT a utility class. Our utilities are pretty much on par with that of a wizzard, and only slightly more than that of a necro. the big ones being CotH, Ports, and Summon Corpse, the rest being minimal at best.<br>
<br>
What we lack in comparitavely is defense.  As either raz or silverblade noted (can't remember which atm), we can either have a pet or be invis. One or the other. We also are defenseless after zoning, logging in, or coming back from linkdeath. We have no snare, no root, no fear. All we have is a pet and our nukes, when fighting, and when prepared. our only defense being the pet. 3000ish hp's and hardly any AC on the best ones. we survive on being able to do enough damage to kill the mob before those 3000 hp's are up.<br>
<br>
What gives us a bad rep is our level 34 bolt, and our level 49 pets. Asside from those, were not nearly as over-powering as some would think.<br>
<br>
But, then again, I'm relatively happy with my class, and I don't really care if things get upgraded. Just pointing out that it wouldn't be a bad thing. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9816>Biggerin Allahya</a>, <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28329>Biggidus DaChaCha</a> <br><a href=http://www.forceofvalor.org>Force of Valor</a> & <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btunareguildalliance>Tunare Guild Alliance</a><br>
Quote of the Whenever:<br>

"A good pun is it's own reword.
"

<br>
<br>
-the master of typos</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucorlathist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>corlathist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/02 10:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fixing Magicians</span><hr size=1> <br>
One side problem to the indifferent problem is single pulls.<br>
<br>
Now social mobs will aid thier compatriots but not if they are light blue or green.  So any mob light blue to the pet's level would be single pet pullable.<br>
<br>
The other single pull problem would be in areas where mobs are not social to each other, yet agro.<br>
So you could invis, pass a bunch of agro mobs, and pull a mob with your pet from deeper in the dungeon, past other agro mobs. <br>
<br>
Still I do like the idea.  However, the more intresting would be to change the code so mobs its flagged indifferent until it attacks.  (Indifferent dropped like Invis)<br>
and then is restored when pet sits for 10 seconds.<br>
A spell that drops like invis does on attack would be easier but would require the mage to mem it and cast it.<br>
<br>
Ironically I agree the 2 most broken classes in EQ are Mages and Druids.  50+.  If fixing nuke power of these classes was the solution Wizard Nukes would have to be better scaled in consistancy.<br>
<br>
Problem is Wizard Nukes don't scale Mana-Damage ratio always up.  If it did, it easy.  Make a Druids &amp; Mages<br>
ratios be 4 levels (1 Scale) or so behind a Wizard.<br>
<br>
Wizard 60 gets 4.0 Ratio.<br>
Wizard 57 gets 3.33 Ratio<br>
<br>
So 60 Mage &amp; 60 Druid Nuke should have a 3.33 Ratio.<br>
Moonfire for example could do 1500 Damage.<br>
<br>
Now, if you upgraded Druid/Mage Nukes to be 1 &quot;level&quot; behind.  You'd have to upgrade Wizard Nukes to each level set have variety.  In another words, you'd need to add nukes so Wizards always have a fire, magic, and cold based nuke with same ratio available at same level.<br>
<br>
You never want a situation where the master nukers<br>
are using a lower level spell and reduced to same mana efficiency of the 2 back up nukers.  (Not including Lures which you sacrifice damage ratio for resists)<br>
<br>
Problem with this solution, is youd have to fundamentally change all wizard, druid, and mage nukes to follow this scaling and level issues consistantly from 1 to 60.<br>
<br>
Then you'd scale other nukes to be &quot;2&quot; or &quot;3&quot; scale sets behind.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Scale Table Could Look Like<br>
W60(3)<br>
<br>
W57(3)  D60(2) M60(2 Bolt)<br>
<br>
W54(3)  D57(2) M57(2 Bolt) M60(2 DD) S60(1) N60(Anti) C60(Anti)<br>
<br>
W51(3)  D54(2) M54(2 Bolt) M57(DD) S57(1) S60(1) N57(Anti) N60(1) C60(1) E60(1) C57(Anti)<br>
<br>
W49(3)  D51(2) M51(2Bolt) M54(DD) S54(1) S57(1)<br>
N54(anti) N57(1) C57(1) E57(1) C54(anti)<br>
<br>
etc<br>
the number in parenthesis would be the number of spells available for different resists at that ratio.  So a Wizard at each set would have a fire/ice/magic nuke choice.  So they can always have a usuable spell.  <br>
<br>
Mage/Druid would have 2 choices.  Fire/Ice likely.  So they Usually have a choice.  (Granted mages would be bolts with dds an additional set behind)<br>
<br>
Shamans would only have one choice.  So when its not usuable they fall an additional level behind.<br>
<br>
Necro/Clerics would be anti-spells.  With Generic spells another level behind.<br>
<br>
Etc Etc.<br>
<br>
One problem might be Levels 49 to 50.  That for 2 Levels<br>
Wizard would only have a 2 Level Adv, rather than 4 Level Advantage they would have at every other point.<br>
<br>
Another Problem would be Stun.  But again you'd address this by scaling another level behind.  So a 57<br>
Druid Spell with Stun would use the Level 51 Wizard Scale.<br>
<br>
You could make a 2nd Chart With consist casting times,<br>
recast delays.  And again the same consistant scaling.<br>
<br>
Only problem is youd have to adjust the spells from Level 1 to 60.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
